               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. WELLS</hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">conducted the Prosecution.</hi>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18650410-name-588" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18650410-name-588" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18650410-name-588" type="surname" value="HEATH"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18650410-name-588" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>GEORGE HEATH</persName>
                  </hi>. I live at Rushy-green, Lewisham, and am a cattle dealer—on the 7th February I turned four horses out to graze in a field in Stansted-lane, Lewisham—one was a grey mare—at 4 o'clock in the after<lb></lb>noon on the 8th February I saw them safe in the field, and on the 10th the grey mare was gone—she is worth about 10<hi rend="italic">l</hi>.—I next saw the mare in Mr. Peplow's possession on 22d February.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18650410-name-589" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18650410-name-589" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18650410-name-589" type="surname" value="SIMPSON"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18650410-name-589" type="given" value="JESSE SAMUEL"></interp>JESSE SAMUEL SIMPSON</persName>
                  </hi> I live at Bell-green, Lewisham—I have known this field in Stansted lane for twelve years—I had charge of the horses for Mr. Heath—the grey mare was in the field on the night of the 9th of February.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18650410-name-590" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18650410-name-590" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18650410-name-590" type="surname" value="PEPLOW"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18650410-name-590" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN PEPLOW</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a cab proprietor, of Cumberland-place, Old Kent-road—on the 10th February, about 11 in the morning, the prisoner came to me—he had a grey mare with him, and he asked me if I would buy it—he said he wanted 4<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. 10<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. for her—I said I could not give him so much, as it was very lame, but I would give him 2<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. 10<hi rend="italic">s</hi>—he said he came by her by "chopping" with a baker at Plumstead for a pony—he said the mare had been turned out on Plumstead marshes.</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="186504100184"></xptr>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner. Q.</hi> Did not I agree to take the mare back again? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Yes, but I told you I was not going to sell her—you did not tell me you had ex<lb></lb>changed her at Croydon-market.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18650410-name-591" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18650410-name-591" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18650410-name-591" type="surname" value="CROUCH"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18650410-name-591" type="given" value="ALFRED JOHN"></interp>ALFRED JOHN CROUCH</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">Policeman, R</hi> 92). I apprehended the prisoner on 21st February at Deptford—I told him it was for stealing a horse on the Thursday week previous—he said he had changed a pony for the grey mare at Croydon-market—I asked him to describe the man, and he said he was a man of about five feet six or seven inches, who wore a <hi rend="italic">billycock</hi> hat, and a long gown—on the road to the station I asked him what he said to the party he sold it to, and he said he told him he had got it of a baker at Erith.</p>
